Package: linux-image-unsigned-6.13-rc4-0-qcom-x1e
Build-Profiles: <!stage1>
Architecture: arm64
Section: kernel
Priority: optional
Provides: linux-image, fuse-module, kvm-api-4, ${linux:rprovides}
Depends: ${misc:Depends}, ${shlibs:Depends}, kmod, linux-base (>= 4.5ubuntu1~16.04.1), linux-modules-6.13-rc4-0-qcom-x1e
Recommends: grub-efi-arm64 [arm64], initramfs-tools | linux-initramfs-tool
Breaks: flash-kernel (<< 3.90ubuntu2) [arm64 armhf], s390-tools (<< 2.3.0-0ubuntu3) [s390x]
Conflicts: linux-image-6.13-rc4-0-qcom-x1e
Suggests: fdutils, linux-qcom-x1e-tools, linux-headers-6.13-rc4-0-qcom-x1e, linux-modules-extra-6.13-rc4-0-qcom-x1e
Description: Linux kernel image for version 6.13-rc4 on ARMv8 SMP
 This package contains the unsigned Linux kernel image for version 6.13-rc4 on
 ARMv8 SMP.
 .
 Supports Snapdragon X Elite processors.
 .
 Geared toward desktop systems.
 .
 You likely do not want to install this package directly. Instead, install
 the linux-qcom-x1e meta-package, which will ensure that upgrades work
 correctly, and that supporting packages are also installed.

